<subSubSection id="4EE68F3717D517B4DE32E3C2E6EEE782" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnostic description">
<paragraph id="E522384A328758393D090C3E0630193A" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5320B4D9EE52B58266F537C322987ADA" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="ED388851788F7CE0F388983EF34B8072" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Mandible lacinia mobilis a stemmed, distally expanded, smooth blade</emphasis>
. Maxilla 1 inner plate with pappose setae lining inner margin; palp 2-articulate. Maxilla 2 inner and outer plates subequal in width, inner plate slightly shorter than outer. Maxilliped palp article 4 reduced or well developed. Gnathopod 1 coxa large, margins diverging distally; basis slender, linear; dactylus small, simple, highly modified with apical tip. 
<emphasis id="9FD2187911E19F40B5CAF6045755C394" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pereopod 3 carpus compressed, wider than long</emphasis>
. Pereopod 4 coxa with weakly-developed, subacutely produced posteroventral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0B0F9926813C32A51F67EDE039250562" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8DD4F26FDE000DD9A5C8576A10946F60" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D77FBBE9EC16ABEA78B488907342B05" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="56F5904E0FD8C2953D1F0EBF8393C065" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7B77A539486BECCB08C91E56D4B7AD3F" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has some variable characters, most importantly the absence of a molar in 
<taxonomicName id="E2451393454A2773C345142CBD2A32E6" authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis id="BDF47C772D614BE9FF9C1AF1000559CF" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(present in the both 
<taxonomicName id="3F1C93C3223FB6216B8D22D86A4FBC4C" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis id="C794A0BE1181D2A5EAE4F040489396D2" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E3013EE738F4FC6566FC22F49F75FB0E" baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis id="355BC6CFC54204AD67C701767D7F3852" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the blunt, reduced maxilliped palp article 4 in 
<taxonomicName id="41CADACDFC018C490FC870CEB0B8201C" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis id="24DF916D5299B3CB397C5AF69A198912" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(well-developed in the other two species). Nevertheless, the distinctively compressed carpus of pereopods 3 and 4, as well as the stemmed and distally expanded lacinia mobilis are strong diagnostic characters which separate these taxa from other groups.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
